{#
  Shared page header — Wave 1 of the UI redesign (2026-06-03).
  Tool pages (Today, Deals, Merchants list, Funders, Upload, Intake,
  Review Queue) replace their inline .deck markup with this include
  during Wave 2. The dossier (merchant_detail_dossier.html.j2) keeps
  its bespoke .masthead since it carries the editorial 92px scale.

  Renders the existing .deck structure exactly — no new CSS needed
  (the `.deck` / `.deck h1` / `.deck h1 em` / `.deck .meta` /
  `.deck .actions` rules in aegis-tool.css already style this shape).
  This partial only centralizes the markup.

  Inputs (all required unless marked optional):
    title       — string, page title (becomes <h1>)
    subtitle    — string, optional em-tagged subtitle inside h1
    meta        — string, optional small-caps meta line on the right
    actions     — list of {label, href, variant?} dicts, optional;
                  variant is one of "primary" | "ghost" | None (default
                  is the existing .btn behavior — no special class)

  Example caller (Wave 2 form to adopt) — straight-set pattern:
    {% set title = "Today" %}
    {% set subtitle = "· attention queue" %}
    {% set meta = now %}
    {% set actions = [{"label": "Upload PDF", "href": "/ui/upload",
                       "variant": "primary"}] %}
    {% include "_page_header.html.j2" with context %}

  ── BLOCK-CAPTURE PATTERN ──────────────────────────────────────────
  When the subtitle, meta, or actions area needs richer markup than a
  string (e.g. an inline counter, a chip, an HTMX trigger button),
  capture a Jinja block into a variable and pass it as the input. The
  partial renders the variable's contents inside the same .deck shape.

    -- Capture rich subtitle markup --
    {% set subtitle %}
      · attention queue
      <span class="chip warn">{{ flagged_count }} flagged</span>
    {% endset %}

    -- Capture rich meta markup --
    {% set meta %}
      {{ rows|length }} rows ·
      <span class="mono-cell">last sync {{ last_sync_at }}</span>
    {% endset %}

    -- Capture a custom actions row (overrides the list-of-dicts form) --
    {% set actions_html %}
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/ui/export">Export CSV</a>
      <button class="btn primary"
              hx-post="/ui/refresh"
              hx-target="#queue">Refresh</button>
    {% endset %}

    {% include "_page_header.html.j2" with context %}

  The partial accepts either the structured `actions` list OR a
  pre-rendered `actions_html` string — `actions_html` wins if both
  are provided.

  ── FUTURE: BLOCK-OVERRIDE FORM ────────────────────────────────────
  If a future refactor moves _page_header.html.j2 from an {% include %}
  to a child template + {% block subtitle %} / {% block actions %}
  override, the same calling-template variables port over with a
  `{% block subtitle %}{{ subtitle }}{% endblock %}` wrapper in this
  partial. Until then, the {% set %} + {% include %} pattern above is
  the canonical form.
#}
<header class="deck">
  <h1>{{ title }}{% if subtitle %} <em>{{ subtitle }}</em>{% endif %}</h1>
  {% if meta %}<div class="meta">{{ meta }}</div>{% endif %}
  {% if actions_html is defined and actions_html %}
    <div class="actions">{{ actions_html }}</div>
  {% elif actions %}
    <div class="actions">
      {% for a in actions %}
        <a class="btn{% if a.variant %} {{ a.variant }}{% endif %}" href="{{ a.href }}">{{ a.label }}</a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  {% endif %}
</header>
